Overall, I like the package, but it often needs better documentation, not because features are not documented but because it&amp;rsquo;s hard to find what you are looking for.
Cells references are an example of this, but it is a critical topic for this package, so those are the ways I&amp;rsquo;ve discovered to sum a column of values.
To do so, I&amp;rsquo;ll take the example of page 19 of the package documentation.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Gopass 1.15 in Fedora 37</title><link>https://fale.io/blog/2022/12/21/gopass-1_15-in-fedora-37</link><media:content type="image/webp" medium="image" width="728" height="350" url="https://fale.io/img/posts/2022_12_21_gopass_115_in_fedora_37.webp"/><pubDate>Wed, 21 Dec 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://fale.io/blog/2022/12/21/gopass-1_15-in-fedora-37</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Back in April, I &lt;a href="https://fale.io/blog/2022/04/25/gopass-in-fedora"&gt;announced&lt;/a&gt; the availability of gopass in the Fedora repositories.
