&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;x509: failed to load system roots and no roots provided
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This message is remembering you that you forgot to provide &lt;strong&gt;Root Certificate Authorities&lt;/strong&gt; to your application.
There are two different ways to solve this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;mount the &lt;em&gt;/etc/ssl/certs&lt;/em&gt; folder from the machine where the container is running&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;bundling the root CAs in your image&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As you may imagine from the title, I believe that the second option is by far better than the first one.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Why SMS should never be used as second factor</title><link>https://fale.io/blog/2018/06/27/why-sms-should-never-be-used-as-second-factor</link><media:content type="image/webp" medium="image" width="728" height="350" url="https://fale.io/img/posts/2018_06_27_why_sms_should_never_be_used_as_second_factor.webp"/><pubDate>Wed, 27 Jun 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://fale.io/blog/2018/06/27/why-sms-should-never-be-used-as-second-factor</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Lately, all website are urging their users to enable second-factors.
