The possible factors are three:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Why everything will end up in a container</title><link>https://fale.io/blog/2018/05/09/why-everything-will-end-up-in-a-container</link><media:content type="image/webp" medium="image" width="728" height="350" url="https://fale.io/img/posts/2018_05_09_why_everything_will_end_up_in_a_container.webp"/><pubDate>Wed, 09 May 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://fale.io/blog/2018/05/09/why-everything-will-end-up-in-a-container</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A couple of months ago, I wrote a blog post about &lt;a href="https://fale.io/blog/2018/03/27/why-containerization-is-not-always-the-answer"&gt;why containerization is not always the answer&lt;/a&gt; and I&amp;rsquo;ve received quite a few comments about it.
