&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Ansible Tower configuration&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;config&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;vm&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;provision&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;ansible&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;ansible&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;ansible&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;playbook&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;#34;playbook.yaml&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I basically create a 2Gb of RAM machine leveraging libvirt and run an Ansible Playbook on it.
The reason I created a 2Gb of RAM machine and I&amp;rsquo;ve not tried to shrink it further is because the Ansible Tower installation checks for 2Gb of RAM, and I wanted to create something easy.
I&amp;rsquo;m sure I could patch the installer to accept a 1Gb machine, but it&amp;rsquo;s not worth the effort to me. Also, in my usual usage of the computer I rarely go below 11Gb free memory, so I&amp;rsquo;m not too concerned in giving 2Gb to my VM.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>AnsibleFest London 2017</title><link>https://fale.io/blog/2017/06/23/ansiblefest-london-2017</link><media:content type="image/webp" medium="image" width="728" height="350" url="https://fale.io/img/posts/2017_06_23_ansiblefest_london_2017.webp"/><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://fale.io/blog/2017/06/23/ansiblefest-london-2017</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This year, I decided to go to AnsibleFest.
