&lt;p&gt;The manual for mail reports this as mail usage prototype:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;mail -r &lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;sender&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; -s &lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;subject&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; receiver-1&lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;,receiver-2,...,receiver-n&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt; &amp;gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;File with the body&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I think all the parameters are pretty straightforward except the &amp;ldquo;File with the body&amp;rdquo; one. This has to be an ASCII file (ie: .txt) with the e-mail body content in the text-only mode.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>CompTIA Network+ Training Kit (Exam N10-005) by Craig Zacker (Microsoft Press)</title><link>https://fale.io/blog/2013/01/01/comptia-network-training-kit-exam-n10-005-by-craig-zacker-microsoft-press</link><media:content type="image/webp" medium="image" width="728" height="350" url="https://fale.io/img/posts/2013_01_01_book_comptia_network_plus_training_kit.webp"/><pubDate>Tue, 01 Jan 2013 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://fale.io/blog/2013/01/01/comptia-network-training-kit-exam-n10-005-by-craig-zacker-microsoft-press</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Reading this book has helped me a lot understanding better how the networking works.
